==German==
===Etymology===
from a Germanic root ''*skeit-a-'', this from an Indo-European root ''*skei-d-'' with the meaning "to [[part]]" (as in {{Gr.}} ''Σχιστός'').

===Noun===
'''Scheiße''' ''f''
#(vulgar) [[shit]]
#:''Wo ich hintrete nur '''Scheiße'''!''
#(vulgar) (figuratively) [[shit]]
#:''Das ist doch alles '''Scheiße'''!''

